content:
I got my Echo Show primarily to see how useful it would be for keeping recipes in front of me while I cook.  I am actually find the Echo Show more useful than I expected it to be.  I have several times used the Food Network and All Recipes skills to find new recipes.  One of the device's best features is its timers - specifically its ability to run simultaneous timers with different labels on each.

I find that I use the Show more than I expected.  I sometimes ask it to update me on the news or to reorder things I have bought from Amazon.  I also use the Echo to add items to my shopping list as I use the last of them.  The other feature I use more than I expected is Echo Show's Uber skill, which allows me to order an Uber car with just a voice prompt.

There are few things on my wish list for Echo Show:

An ability to forward recipes from any source to the device;

Better sound quality for listening to music;

An easy way to add multiple items to my shopping list - i.e. without needing to precede each item by saying  'Alexa';

Refinement to the Uber skill.  Currently, if you order an Uber via the show you can not tell it (or, until he or she arrives, the driver) your destination.
